      • char2FloatEntrySet

        public ObjectSet<Char2FloatMap.Entry> char2FloatEntrySet()
        Description copied from interface: Char2FloatMap
        Returns a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.

        This method is necessary because there is no inheritance along type parameters: it is thus impossible to strengthen Char2FloatMap.entrySet() so that it returns an ObjectSet of type-specific entries (the latter makes it possible to access keys and values with type-specific methods).

        Specified by:
        char2FloatEntrySet in interface Char2FloatMap
        Returns:
        a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.
